sentences: Berta Alves de Sousa (8 April 1906 – 1 August 1997) was a Portuguese pianist and composer.

After completing her studies, Alves de Sousa took a position at the Music Conservatory of Oporto in 1946 teaching chamber music, (she later became chair) and performed as a concert pianist, accompanist and conductor.
In 1941 she won the Prix de Sa Moreira established by Orpheon Portuense.
Numérica 1999, Sofia Lourenço, Compositores Portugueses Contemporâneos
